## PolySyncIterable.prepend() method

Return a new iteration that will iterate over `other`<!-- -->, then over `this`<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
prepend<U>(other: Iterable<U>): PolySyncIterable<T | U>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  other | Iterable&lt;U&gt; | Iterable to be prepended |

<b>Returns:</b>

PolySyncIterable&lt;T \| U&gt;

a new [PolySyncIterable](./polyethylene.polysynciterable.md) that yields the elements of `other` and then the elements of `this`

## Remarks

The resulting iteration is of the combined generic type of `this` and `other`<!-- -->, allowing this method to merge the types of two distinct iterables.
